Migrants who come to Britain to live or work must prove they have not committed a crime in the previous ten years under new measures to tighten up the nation’s borders.

Foreigners from outside the EU will be forced to provide a criminal records certificate from their home country before being given a visa to enter the UK, the Mail can reveal.

Ministers hope to bolster existing checks to prevent serious and violent criminals from being allowed to enter the UK.

